commit.message:
Fix for macOS build failing on Monterey (#278)

Fixed an issue in cmake/FindPolarSSL.cmake where the system's
C compiler would be called directly without the shim to provide
access to standard system libraries. With this fix, building
on macOS no longer fails to find stdio.h ;)

Check return value from argument parsing and exit if -1

Fixes an use heap after free crash when the user, for example, forgets a 'u' in front of the password :)

commit.message:
cmake: allow building without FUSE

The main feature of Dislocker is mounting an encrypted volume using
FUSE, but the dislocker-{file,metadata,bek} programs can still be
built without FUSE.

The current build system is somewhat broken if FUSE can't be found.
find_package(FUSE) can fail and configuration will continue anyway, then
dislocker-fuse.c is unconditionally compiled which will fail without
fuse.h.

Add a cmake boolean option WITH_FUSE (defaults to ON) that can be used
to turn off FUSE support. Without FUSE, the main dislocker(-fuse) binary
is not compiled or installed. When FUSE is ON, the cmake configuration
will fail if FUSE cannot be found, rather than passing the buck on to
a compiler error.

cmake: allow explicitly disabling Ruby bindings

Users may wish to build Dislocker without Ruby even if it's installed on
the system. This is useful for packagers, or users who don't want to
recompile Dislocker every time their package manager updates Ruby.

Add a new WITH_RUBY cmake option that can be set to ON, OFF, or AUTO.
AUTO (the default) behaves as Dislocker does currently - check for Ruby
and use it if found, ON requires Ruby and fails if not found, and OFF
never checks for Ruby and disables the bindings.
